Yesterday I assigned six hours for practising their songs on my cor anglais, clarinet, E-flat clarinet, bass clarinet and bassoon. I practised with my friends who played triangle, tambourine, castanets, sleigh bells and cymbals, all of which have indefinite pitch. Adding these instruments makes the music more rhythmic. Saxophone, cor anglais and clarinet are transposing instruments. Flute is a reedless instrument.
